rComments: Whispers in class and expects his students to agree with everything he says.
I haven't taken a class with Prof. A, but he is on my committee, and is absolutely fabulous: very helpful, patient, clear, supportive, friendly, honest, and so on.  Just my 2 cents.

Took this course years ago, and forget the # but not the prof, so write from memory. He knwos his stuff, doesn't tolerate fools or lazy sods, but encourages the student who shows interest & effort. So glad I took his class!

He's unpredictable, like a passive bully. Has a doormat in his office that says 'go away.' Not funny, really. Intimidates students, seen as pompous... and he's really hard to understand in class because he WHISPERS his lectures. Professor, improve thyself
